# 1. Monolithic Architecture

==================================================

Monolithic architecture is a **software design pattern where all functionalities of an application are developed and deployed as a single application**.

All modules are tightly integrated and run in **one codebase and one deployment unit**.

------------------------------
## Example: Banking Application
-------------------------------

Modules inside same application

• Net Banking
• Mobile Banking
• Credit Card Services
• Debit Card Services
• Customer Management
• Transactions

===================================
## Monolithic Architecture Diagram
===================================

```
                +-----------------------+
                |     Client / User     |
                +----------+------------+
                           |
                           v
                +-----------------------+
                |   Monolithic App      |
                |-----------------------|
                | Net Banking Module    |
                | Mobile Banking Module |
                | Credit Card Module    |
                | Debit Card Module     |
                | Customer Module       |
                +-----------+-----------+
                            |
                            v
                      +-----------+
                      | Database  |
                      +-----------+
```

All modules run inside **one application**.

==================================================

# Challenges With Monolithic Architecture

==================================================

----------------------
## 1. Tight Coupling
----------------------

All modules are connected together.

If we modify one module it may impact other modules.

Example

```
Change in Credit Card module
        ↓
May impact Payment module
```

-------------------------
## 2. Deployment Issues
-------------------------

If we make a small change, we must deploy the **entire application**.

Example

```
Bug in Debit Card module
→ Need to redeploy whole Banking application
```

---------------------------
## 3. Scalability Issues
---------------------------

We cannot scale individual modules.

Example

```
High traffic on Payments

But we must scale entire application
instead of scaling only Payment module
```

----------------------------
## 4. Maintenance Complexity
----------------------------

As application grows

• Codebase becomes very large
• Hard to understand
• Hard to maintain

---------------------------
## 5. Technology Dependency
---------------------------

Whole application must use the **same technology stack**.

Example

```
Backend → Java
Frontend → JSP
```

Introducing new technologies becomes difficult.

-------------------
## 6. Server Burden
-------------------

Entire application runs on **single server**.

Heavy load can slow down system.

----------------------------
## 7. Single Point of Failure
-----------------------------

If the application crashes, the **entire system stops**.

Example

```
Payment module failure
→ Whole banking system down
```

