# Admin Server

================

Admin Server is used to **monitor and manage all microservices from a single dashboard**.

It provides a **centralized monitoring UI** where we can see the status of all running services.

In Spring Boot microservices, **Spring Boot Admin** is commonly used.

It collects monitoring information using **Spring Boot Actuator**.

-----------------------------
## Why Admin Server is Used
------------------------------
In microservices architecture, there may be **many services running simultaneously**.

Instead of checking each service individually, Admin Server allows us to **monitor everything in one place**.

----------------------------------------
## Information Available in Admin Server
------------------------------------------

Admin Server can display the following information:

--------------------
### 1. Health Check
---------------------

Shows whether the service is running properly.

Example

UP
DOWN
OUT_OF_SERVICE

--------------------------------
### 2. Configuration Properties
--------------------------------

Displays configuration values loaded by the microservice.

Example

Database URL
Kafka Configuration
Redis Configuration
Application Properties

--------------------
### 3. Beans Loaded
--------------------

Shows all **Spring Beans** loaded in the application.

Example

Service Beans
Controller Beans
Repository Beans
Configuration Beans

--------------------
### 4. URL Mappings
--------------------

Displays all available **API endpoints**.

Example

/users
/orders
/products
/payments

------------------------
### 5. Logger Management
-------------------------

We can **change log levels dynamically** without restarting the application.

Example

INFO
DEBUG
ERROR
TRACE
WARN

-----------------------------
## Admin Server Architecture
------------------------------
```
    +----------------------+
    |    Admin Server      |
    |   Monitoring UI      |
    +----------+-----------+
               |
  --------------------------------
  |              |               |
  v              v               v
```

+-----------+   +-----------+   +-----------+
| User MS   |   | Order MS  |   | Payment MS|
| Actuator  |   | Actuator  |   | Actuator  |
+-----------+   +-----------+   +-----------+

Admin Server collects monitoring data from **Actuator endpoints of each microservice**.

