## Config Server

================

Config Server is used to externalize and centralize configuration properties of microservices.

Instead of keeping configuration files inside each microservice, they are stored in a central configuration server.

This helps separate:

Application Code
Application Configuration

This makes microservices loosely coupled with configuration files.

Why Config Server is Used

In microservices architecture there may be many services.

Without Config Server:

Each service has its own application.properties or application.yml.

With Config Server:

All configuration is stored in one centralized location.

Config Server Architecture
            +----------------------+
            |     Config Server    |
            | Central Configuration|
            +----------+-----------+
                       |
    ----------------------------------------
    |                |                     |
    v                v                     v

+-----------+ +-----------+ +-----------+
| Service A | | Service B | | Service C |
+-----------+ +-----------+ +-----------+

All microservices fetch configuration from Config Server at startup.

Example configurations stored:

Database configuration
Kafka configuration
Redis configuration
Application properties
Environment variables

