## Feign Client

===============

Feign Client is used for inter-service communication between microservices.

When one microservice needs to call another microservice, we use Feign Client.

Feign Client is provided by the Spring Cloud library.

It is a declarative REST client, meaning we just define an interface and Spring automatically generates the REST call.

Example

Order Service needs to call Payment Service.

Instead of writing REST template code manually, we use Feign Client.

Example:

@FeignClient(name = "PAYMENT-SERVICE")
public interface PaymentClient {

@GetMapping("/payment/{id}")
Payment getPayment(@PathVariable Long id);

}

Feign automatically sends the request to the target microservice.

Feign Client Architecture
       +-------------+
       | Order MS    |
       +------+------+
              |
         Feign Client
              |
              v
       +-------------+
       | Payment MS  |
       +-------------+

This simplifies microservice-to-microservice communication.

